# Project Walkthrough: AI Slideshow Generator

## 🚀 Recent Updates: Timeline Layout & Visual Polish

We have successfully resolved the layout issues on the Timeline slide and finalized the editor experience.

### 1. Timeline Slide Repair
-   **Problem**: Content was jammed at the top ("weird spacing") and overflowing horizontally.
-   **Solution**:
    -   **Grid Architecture**: Switched to a fixed 3-column grid (`grid-cols-3`) to guarantee perfect alignment for up to 3 items per row.
    -   **Vertical Centering**: The entire timeline now floats in the optical center of the slide (`flex-1 items-center justify-center`).
    -   **Editable Fields**: Added [EditableText](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Editor/EditableText.tsx#12-62) to Dates, Titles, and Descriptions, so you can fix any AI text weirdness instantly.

### 2. Auto-Scaling Engine (New Feature)
-   **Problem**: Slides were fixed at 1920x1080, causing them to overflow or look cut off on smaller screens.
-   **Solution**: Implemented a `ResizeObserver` system in the main layout.
    -   Automatically detects available screen space.
    -   Dynamically calculates the perfect `scale` (e.g., 0.65) to fit the HD slide entirely within the view.

### 3. Clean Editor Interface
-   **Problem**: Raw "Choose File" inputs and visual clutter ruined the slide aesthetics.
-   **Solution**:
    -   **Hidden Inputs**: Completely removed visible file inputs.
    -   **Contextual UI**: "Upload" and "Change Image" buttons now **only appear on hover/drag**.

## Architecture Status
-   **Frontend**: React + Tailwind + Auto-Scaling
-   **Backend**: Node.js (Crawler Service)
-   **AI**: Gemini 2.0 Flash (JSON-based generation)

## Verification
-   **Build**: Successful (`npm run build` passed).
-   **Code Validation**: Confirmed Grid layout logic in [TimelineSlide.tsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Templates/TimelineSlide.tsx).
